DOS-PORT (patch 0093, Phase 9 wave 21 Lever G default-flip). Polarity
flip of patch 0092. Mirrors the wave-18 0086→0088 (DIRECT_VESA) and
wave-17.6 0085 (PREVFRAME_DIFF) two-stage rollout patterns.

Wave 21 outcomes leading to this patch:
- W21A real-HW measured Lever G mechanism working (per spec § 1).
  Fps gain: -26.6 ms/flip vs Tier-1 baseline in heavy-music scenes.
- W21A audio-quality regression: "slow + distorted music" surfaced.
- Slot 0094 fixed the root cause (Organya stereo-vs-mono mismatch at
  the _musicCallback boundary).
- Post-0094 fps gain settles into spec's predicted range (~+11 fps in
  heavy-music scenes; W21A's pre-fix -26.6 ms figure was inflated by
  the half-speed playback artifact).
- W21B real-HW listening test confirmed Tier-2 audio quality
  user-acceptable per direction 2026-05-05 (mono-11025 trade for
  +11 fps accepted).

Wave 21 patch 0093 promotes Tier-2 to DEFAULT-ON. The
SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_AUDIO_TIER2 env var keeps its name but inverts its
semantics:
  - default (unset / empty / "1" / any non-"0"): Tier-2 ENGAGED
    (11025 Hz mono, 256-frame buffer, ~43 Hz IRQ rate)
  - "0" (literal): killswitch reverts to Tier-1 baseline (22050 Hz
    stereo, original Cave Story 2004 spec; full audio quality, ~+11 fps
    fps gain forfeited)

This is the inverse of wave-16+ "strict 1-only enables" convention.
Mirrors patch 0088's `_abl_direct_vesa()` killswitch logic (and
patch 0085's PREVFRAME_DIFF polarity flip pattern) — single env var
lets a user revert to bisect-able prior behaviour without a rebuild.

Implementation:

1. `SoundManager.cpp::SoundManager::init()` env-helper polarity:
   ```cpp
   const bool tier2_on = !(tier2 && tier2[0] == '0' && tier2[1] == 0);
   ```
   (was `tier2 && tier2[0] == '1' && tier2[1] == 0` for opt-in).
   Default ON; only literal "0" disables.

2. LOG_INFO init banner messages updated:
   - ENABLED branch (= default since wave 21 patch 0093) now references
     "default since wave 21 patch 0093" + "set =0 to revert" rather
     than "experimental opt-in".
   - DISABLED branch references the killswitch + spec-§-1-original-
     22050-stereo + "trades fps for fidelity" framing.

3. No SAMPLE_RATE / AUDIO_CHANNELS code changes — those externs
   already exist from 0092. Buffer-pin logic unchanged. Pixtone
   resample-spec sites + Organya callback (patch 0094) unchanged.

4. docs/BOOT.md edit: AUDIO_TIER2 entry MOVED from "User-facing
   options" (where 0092 placed it as opt-in) to "Compatibility /
   fallback options" (where killswitches live, alongside DIRTY_RECTS
   / PIXEL_FORMAT_8 / BACKDROP_CACHE / DIRECT_VESA). Documents the
   `=0` killswitch + "for hardware above Tier 1 reference / purist
   playthroughs" use case.

What stays unchanged from 0092:
- Runtime SAMPLE_RATE / AUDIO_CHANNELS extern variable plumbing
- Buffer pin to 256 frames via SDL_HINT_AUDIO_DEVICE_SAMPLE_FRAMES
  OVERRIDE (load-bearing for IRQ-rate-halving mechanism)
- 10 channel-count substitution sites in Pixtone + Organya
- Singleton-init ordering (env check → MIX_CreateMixerDevice → lazy
  Pixtone/Organya construction picks up runtime values)

What stays unchanged from 0094:
- Mono-downmix logic in Organya::_musicCallback (averages L+R per
  output frame when AUDIO_CHANNELS == 1)
- Tier-1 path bit-identical to pre-0094

Risk: low. The path itself is identical to 0092+0094's; only the
gate's default flips. If a regression surfaces on a fingerprint we
haven't tested, the user can `SET SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_AUDIO_TIER2=0`
and reboot to recover Tier-1.

Test plan:
- Build-qa DOSBox-X smoke (3 configs):
  A. env-unset (default Tier-2 engaged; verify Tier-2 init log + 256
     buffer + Pixtone regen at 11025).
  B. AUDIO_TIER2=1 explicit (same as A; bit-identical to default).
  C. AUDIO_TIER2=0 killswitch (Tier-1 reverted; same audio quality
     as wave-17.6 baseline).
- No new real-HW iter needed — W21A measured the fps mechanism +
  W21B validated audio quality. Polarity flip is a 1-line semantic
  change, no behavioral surprises.

User-facing impact:
- New users get +11 fps with the audio quality trade out-of-the-box.
- Power users / purists set `=0` to keep original 22050 stereo audio.
- README / CHANGELOG should document the new default (team-lead
  coordinating the README update separately).

Reference:
  patches/nxengine-evo/0086-perf-wave-18-direct-vesa-hotpath.patch
  patches/nxengine-evo/0088-perf-wave-20-direct-vesa-default-on.patch
    (canonical two-stage rollout: opt-in 0086 → default-on 0088 with
     `=0` killswitch; this patch is the audio analog)
  patches/nxengine-evo/0085-perf-wave-17-6-prev-frame-diff-default-off.patch
    (precedent for default-OFF polarity flip via killswitch convention)
  patches/nxengine-evo/0092-perf-wave-21-lever-g-tier2-audio-config.patch
    (the Tier-2 implementation this patch promotes to default)
  patches/nxengine-evo/0094-perf-wave-21-lever-g-fix-organya-stereo-mono.patch
    (the audio-quality fix that made the default-flip viable)
  docs/PHASE9-LEVER-G-PLAN.md (Lever G spec § 3 two-stage rollout
    pattern)
  W21A real-HW data (fps measurement)
  W21B real-HW listening test (audio quality verdict)

